              <strong>Why this works:</strong> Explicit role ‚Üí AI understands context. 
              Mandatory reasoning ‚Üí Transparent decisions. Security mandates ‚Üí Built-in guardrails.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">What I Learned Building 3,000 Lines of Prompts:</h3>
            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li><strong>Temperature settings matter:</strong> Creative tasks 0.7-1.0, code generation 0.1-0.3. Most people never adjust this.</li>
              <li><strong>Reasoning transparency prevents hallucinations:</strong> Forcing &lt;THINKING&gt; tags means AI shows its work.</li>
              <li><strong>Security can't be bolted on:</strong> Every agent has security mandates built in.</li>
              <li><strong>Specificity beats generality:</strong> "Generate code passing tests in &lt;INPUT&gt;, adhering to Big O constraints..." not "write good code"</li>
              <li><strong>Agent specialization works:</strong> 12 narrow agents > 1 generalist agent</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

